    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Confirmed Teku is following the spec correctly.  We should probably open an issue on the eth2 specs repo with the suggestion that the current eth1 data is not considered a valid vote and only used as the fallback.\r\n\r\nThat way even if the first proposer has no valid blocks and votes for the current eth1 data block, other proposers would still prefer to vote for data that progresses the eth1 chain rather than just following that vote.  This would also essentially make the current eth1 data vote a replacement for any need to create random votes.",
